questionRound.0.question.9.answer: I would look to see if any of the colors had an obvious course of action because both options of either X or Y were clearly more favorable than the other option  and then I would just work backwards from there  assuming other players would also do the same and act rationally in their own best self-interest.

I would assume that the person depending on my answer would think that I would choose the value that gives me my highest payoff. So the next person would choose his value that would give him the highest payoff accordingly. The person after the person after  me would choose the value that would give him the highest payoff  corresponding to the value the person after me chooses. Finally  my answer is dependant on what the person before chooses  and I would choose the highest value accordingly.
I just looked at what the other players would have picked in their best interest and then accordingly made my choice in a way that it would bring mazimum profits to me.

I just made my decisions off what I thought the other players were going to choose. One of the three or four players always had an obvious choice so I just started there and worked my way to my own choices after going through everyone else's.

check if X or Y has absolute advantages  if yes  then choose the one with absolute advantage. | if no  then look at the person who affects you  see if they have absolute advantage then make decision based on assumption of their actions.

I choose based on looking at what the color to my right choose. I started out at the very right side at the way end  and I predicted that they would choose the choice with higher numbers. Based on their choice  I'd look at the next color to the left of the last color  and I predicted what they'd choose (assuming that they were thinking the same way as me)  and so on.  |  | My decision is really based on whether I can predict what the other players choose  asssuming that they would go for the higher values.

At first I just went for whichever would be best for me  but then since how much you're paid is contingent upon the actions of the other player  I tried to select mine based on what I thought he or she would choose for themselves and then based on my guess for that  which payoff would be greater for me.

I looked for the control color  the one where the decision to choose either X or Y was the most clear-cut and most lucrative. From there  I mapped out one by one on the other charts what each of the others' decisions would be based on that clear-cut decision (and on the assumption that everyone would choose with their own best interests in mind) until I came to my own that would yield the highest possible amount for me.

I could tell what to pick based on what I'd figure everyone else would pick in order to earn themselves the most money. What was frustrating was when I used this process  but others failed and earned me the least amount of money

I thought about the risk that other members might take depending on the earnings they would receive. If the numbers were both high  they would probably choose that option  yet if there was a large difference in the numbers  I assumed they would risk their decision and choose the option with the highest earnings.
In a match  there is always a role who has one choice much better than the other one  so first find out the role's choice  and take advandage of the choice.

I expected most people to expect everyone would play to maximize their earnings so they would choose whatever option got them the most coins when everyone else choose the same optimizing option. If I needed to compromise to my second best option so that a majority got the best I did because I'd otherwise end up with a lower payout.
